\ln |x(t)|-\ln |x(t_0)| = \int_{t_0}^t A(t_1)dt_1.
\dfrac{dx}{dt}=A(t)x 
\implies \int_{\tau}^{t}\dot{x}(t)\mathrm{d}t = \int_{\tau}^{t}A(t)x(t)\mathrm{d}t, \forall t \ge \tau \ge t_0
\implies x(t) =x(\tau)+\int_{\tau}^{t}A(t)x(t)\mathrm{d}t,\forall t \ge \tau \ge t_0\\
\|x(t)\| =\|x(\tau)\|+\int_{\tau}^{t}\|A(t)\| \|x(t)\|\mathrm{d}t,\forall t \ge \tau \ge t_0\\
